<br>
The Talon first flew in get this, 1959! Yep, that’s right folks, this means that the plane was actually in the design phase in probably the mid 50’s. So, NASA in all its glory is using a technology that’s almost 50 years old. But, then again I bet that the designers of the B-52 (they started work on the “BUFF” in the late 40’s BTW) would have flipped out if you told them in 1952 (when the B-52 first flew) that their creation would not only be in frontline USAF service a full 50 years from that date, dropping conventional iron bombs in Afghanistan, but that it would be scheduled to remain in service for another 20 years thence. Do you want me to talk about the C-130 Hercules as well? The C-130 first flew in 1955 and to this day remains in frontline USAF service…oh what’s the use? The point is that we are going backwards not forwards. We should at least have had nuke powered bombers and fighters by now…only in our dreams… <br>
